                            <comment id="14551207" author="rriggs" created="Sat, 14 Jan 2023 12:05:11 -0800"  >The declaration in ProcessImpl_md.c: 370 is for a const pointer, but the memory is always mutable.&lt;br/&gt;
The memory backing the command string is mutable and refs either to a buffer allocated by GetStringChars or is the underlying memory of the string.  Both are mutable.  &lt;br/&gt;
The pointer is cast to (LPWSTR) as it is passed to CreateProcessW. There is not an issue with compiler messages.&lt;br/&gt;
It may be more appropriate to remove the `const` from the declarations.</comment>
